# TCS-Project 

fork the repo from here
![](data:image/png;base64,)

*to clone the repo in your local device*
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/TCS-Project.git


*to add the link of main repo in your local device*
git remote add tcs https://github.com/rshahmeer27/TCS-Project.git

*to pull the git repo*
git pull

*to add the changes in a commit*
git add -A
git commit -m "add message here"

*to push the repo in your forked repo*
git checkout -b branch-name-here 

*to push the branch in your forked repo*
git push -u origin branch-name-here

After pushing the code in the forked repository. Create a pull request from your GitHub account from here

!["Pull request" link above list of files](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-26570/images/help/pull_requests/pull-request-start-review-button.png)

than select the branch you want to merge 
![Compare across forks link](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-10913/images/help/pull_requests/compare-across-forks-link.png)

![Drop-down menus for choosing the base fork and branch](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-44606/images/help/pull_requests/choose-base-fork-and-branch.png)

Dont create a pull request for the main branch of the Repository Shahmeer created, instead create a pull request for the Project branch in the main repo.

![Create pull request button](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-26223/images/help/pull_requests/pullrequest-send.png)

Than create a pull request by clicking this button. 
	 
## additional commands

*to check the linked repos*
git remote -v 

*to check the number of branches in your system and see which branch you are on*
git branch
